                {
                    "name": "Get Selcom Payment Status",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [
                            {
                                "key": "Accept",
                                "value": "application/json",
                                "type": "text"
                            }
                        ],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/payments/{{payment_reference}}/selcom-status",
                            "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                            "path": [
                                "api",
                                "v1",
                                "payments",
                                "{{payment_reference}}",
                                "selcom-status"
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "Queries Selcom API directly to get the current payment status for a given payment reference.\n\n### Path Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description | Example |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|---------|\n| reference | string | Yes | Payment reference (order_id used in Selcom) | a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890 |\n\n### Response\nReturns both Selcom's live status and local payment record:\n- **order_id**: Selcom order identifier\n- **payment_status**: Current Selcom payment status (COMPLETED, FAILED, PENDING, CANCELLED)\n- **amount**: Transaction amount\n- **channel**: Mobile money operator used (MPESATZ, TIGOPESATZ, etc.)\n- **transid**: Selcom transaction ID\n- **result**: Selcom result (SUCCESS, FAILED)\n- **resultcode**: Selcom result code (000 = success)\n- **local_status**: Mapped status from our database (successful, failed, pending, cancelled)\n- **local_payment**: Local payment record details\n\n### Use Cases\n- Check real-time payment status from Selcom\n- Reconcile payment discrepancies\n- Debug payment issues\n- Verify payment completion status\n\n### Error Responses\n- **404**: Payment not found in local database\n- **500**: Error querying Selcom API\n- **401**: Unauthorized (missing or invalid token)"
                    },
